One kind of spicule composes the skeleton, which has no special organisation: the triactine (
Fig. 6
; 
Table 6
). Triactines are equiangular and equiradiate, and their actines are straight and conical, with blunt ends.

C. conifera
n. sp. is very abundant in the Oasis Coralino, particularly in summer. Its habitat is sciaphilous. Specimens are frequently found under rocks or other animals, such as other sponges, tunicates (
Ascidia
) and soft corals (
Palythoa sp.
).
